-- Dubai Government Restructures Dubai World Board, Sheikh Ahmed Is Chairman
-- B y   M a h e r   C h m a y t e l l i
-- 2010-12-12T14:33:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-12/dubai-government-restructures-dubai-world-board-sheikh-ahmed-is-chairman.html
Dubai’s ruler Sheikh Mohammed Bin
Rashid Al Maktoum appointed Sheikh Ahmed bin Saeed Al Maktoum
as the chairman of Dubai World, replacing Ahmed bin Sulayem.  Mohammed Ibrahim al-Shaibani, director general of the
ruler’s court, Ahmad Humaid Al Tayer, governor of Dubai
International Financial Centre, Abdulrahman Al Saleh, director
general of the Department of Finance, and Hamad Buamim, director
general of the Dubai Chamber of Commerce & Industry, were among
those named to the new board, according to an e-mailed statement
from the Dubai government’s Media Office.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  